DistributionClaimed(address,address,addr.details: `actor` is used to differentiate between who is triggering the event emission. Current options are "member" and "manager", but more may be introduced (e.g. "integration").

params.amount: Total amount to be withdrawn, including fees.
params.managerDistributionShareBasisPoints: Share to the syndicate manager in basis points (i.e. as a fraction divided by 10000)
params.syndicateDistributionShareBasisPoints: Distribution share to Syndicate Protocol in basis points (i.e. as a fraction divided by 10000)

returns._0: Tuple of the amounts (toMembers, toSyndicate, toManager) that will be transferred, together adding up to the passed amount.

calculateEligibleDistribution(uint256,ui.details: HIGH RISK: If this calculation is incorrect, a user could withdraw more or less than they are entitled to.

params.depositMember: Member's deposit to the Syndicate at the moment that it was closed by the manager
params.depositTotal: Total deposits (from anyone) to the Syndicate
params.distributionClaimedMember: Value in distributions that user has withdrawn from the fund already.  Make sure this matches the token type of `distributionTotal`.
params.distributionTotal: Total distributions available from the fund, claimed or not.  Make sure this matches the token type of `distributionClaimedMember`.

returns._0: Value in distributions that user is eligible to withdraw

params.distributionERC20Address: The ERC20 address of the token whose distributions are being queried
params.memberAddress: The address of the member whose info is being queried

returns._0: The distribution claimed by a member for a given `distributionERC20Address`

returns._0: The unclaimed distribution for a member for a given `distributionERC20Address`

getSyndicateFeeAddress().details: This function is needed to allow inheriting contracts to only be able to view but not change syndicateFeeAddress without going through ownerSetSyndicateFeeAddress

params.amounts: The amounts to be added to the available distributions of each ERC20 token indexed in `distributionERC20Addresses`. This array must have the same length as `distributionERC20Addresses`.
params.distributionERC20Addresses: The ERC20 contract addresses of the distributions. Distributions can be set for any ERC20 token, including the deposit token.

params.amounts: The amounts to increase the claimed distribution of the corresponding index in memberAddresses. All paramter arrays must match exactly in length.
params.distributionERC20Addresses: The ERC20 contract addresses of the distribution.
params.memberAddresses: The addresses of the members whose info is being set.

memberClaimDistributions(address,address.details: Distribution claims are processed before any fees that an ERC20 token may assess. The amount that all users receive may be lower if an ERC20 token takes a fee upon transfers.

params.ERC20Addresses: The token types to be transferred from the Syndicate to the member. Members may only claim distributions from ERC20 contract addresses that the manager has set for distribution.
params.amounts: The amounts (in token types specified by `distributionERC20Addresses`) to be claimed
params.syndicateAddress: The Syndicate that a member will claim distributions from

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params.feeAddress: The owner's new contract fee address

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

DistributionAdded(address,address,uint25.notice: A manager sets a distribution. It is important that the manager holds such distribution assets in their wallet for members to claim.

DistributionClaimed(address,address,addr.notice: A member claims a distribution by withdrawing their assets or a manager sets a distribution claimed on behalf of a member. Managers can only claim a distribution for a member on modifiable syndicates.

DistributionERC20AddressAdded(address,ad.notice: A manager sets a distribution for a new ERC20 address. This is called by `managerSetDistributions()` the first time a distribution is set for a particular ERC20 address.

SyndicateFeeAddressUpdated(address).notice: The owner updates the contract fee address.

calculateDistributionShares(uint256,uint.notice: Calculates the amount of a distribution that goes to the members, Syndicate Protocol, and the syndicate manager.

calculateEligibleDistribution(uint256,ui.notice: Calculates the maximum value in distribution tokens that a member can withdraw based on their percent ownership of the Syndicate, the total amount of a particular token available for distribution, and the amount of that distribution token that the member has already claimed.

constructor.notice: Used to initialize the Syndicate contract.

getDistributionClaimedMember(address,add.notice: Get a member's claimed distributions for a given ERC20

getDistributionClaimedTotal(address,addr.notice: Get a Syndicate's total claimed distributions for a given ERC20

getDistributionTotal(address,address).notice: Get a Syndicate's total distributions for a given ERC20

getDistributionUnclaimedMember(address,a.notice: Get a member's unclaimed distribution for a given ERC20

getSyndicateFeeAddress().notice: getter function for syndicate fee address.

managerSetDistributions(address,address[.notice: Used by a manager to initialize or increase the available distributions for multiple ERC20 tokens after a Syndicate has been closed.

managerSetDistributionsClaimedForMembers.notice: Used by a manager to modify the claimed distribution amount for a given member addressThis function can only be called if the Syndicate is modifiable. The modifiable boolean is set by the manager on creation and cannot be changed after the Syndicate is created.Claimed distributions can only be raised. If we allowed a manager to lower a member's claimed distributions, the manager's token allowance and token balance may not be enough to cover all future distributions.Claimed distributions cannot exceed the member's eligible distributions as calculated from their deposit. If we allowed a manager to raise a member's claimed distributions above their eligible distributions, we would have to adjust `distributionTotal` accordingly and this would result in every other member being eligible for an additional distribution, which the manager may not have a sufficient allowance/balance to cover.This function can only be called after distributions are enabled. Before distributions are enabled, there is no reason to call this function since there are no distributions available to claim.

memberClaimDistributions(address,address.notice: The member is identified via `msg.sender`. This function must be called from the address associated with the member's deposit.This function may only be called after the Syndicate is closed by the manager, though the Syndicate may be closed for some time before a distribution is set (e.g. after funds have been raised but while they are being used for investments)

ownerSetSyndicateFeeAddress(address).notice: set a new fee address for the contract function that can only be triggered by the contract owner.

ownerTransferOwnership(address).notice: Transfers ownership to the provided address.
